	    ,{"code":"GELI", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Germanium-Lithium detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The experimental set-up consisted"
		,"of four particle telescopes, two 12.7 cm x 12.7 cm"
		,"NaI(Tl) and one Ge(Li) counter. The gamma-ray energy"
		,"resolution of the NaI counters was 7%. The Ge(Li)"
		,"counter had an efficiency of 20% with a resolution of"
		,"2.2 keV at 1.3 MeV. The telescopes were placed at"
		,"50 degree with respect to the beam direction and had"
		,"front and end Si counters with thicknesses of 150 um"
		,"and 3000 um, respectively."]
	}
      ]
